7:
Argh, Clarisse! How many times have 
I told you? Finish calculations BEFORE 
you disintegrate reality—
10: Wait, where the hell am I?
14:
A welcoming party, eh? Not the 
classiest greeting I've ever been given.
17:
Hah. Very well. Before I unlock the 
mysteries of this world, I'll deal with 
these fools. Come, Ouroboros!
20:
Huh? Is my composition off? 
No, that can't be it...
23:
Ah-hah! Of course! A different world 
requires a different methodology.
26:
Hm. What's this filling the air? So even 
the elemental configuration is 
different.
28:
But if we're talking basic physics, small 
discrepancies are irrelevant. All I need 
to do is tweak my formula and—
31:
What a curious place. The sheer 
magnitude of these tremors is 
unnatural.
34:
Oy, idiots, will you PLEASE leave 
a genius to her thoughts?
38: That last tremor was a doozy.
41:
The epicenter was below us. It may 
have started in the depths.
44:
Wow, the depths... I wonder what's 
down there. No one's been able to find 
out yet, right?
47:
I would also like to uncover more 
about them. How do they connect to 
different worlds without the aid of 
a World Flipper?
50:
Do not go needlessly into the depths. 
We are here to train. Seeking 
knowledge comes after.
61:
Hehe! Oooh, mister and miss 
skyfarers!
65:
I think I'm a widdle lost. Do you wanna 
help me?
75:
There are these big, mean monsters, 
and I can't beat them by myself. 
Pleeease?
85:
This is not what we signed up for! 
There's so many of them!
89:
Phew... Finally, I have some breathing 
room to think.
97:
I am the world's cutest, most super 
genius alchemist. I AM the strategy.
100:
Now, let's see... Light and shadow... Fire, 
water, and wind—oh, and thunder?
104:
I'll use those tremors for amplification 
aaand—come forth, Ouroboros! It's 
snack time!
108: H-holy mackerel... That was ONE shot...
113:
One is more than enough! Especially 
since you provided ample distraction. 
Good job, meat shield.
117:
Meat shield? Uh, weren't you nicer like 
five minutes ago?
122:
Whatever could you mean? Cagliostro 
is always cute as a button!
130:
Alk. Do not let down your guard. She is 
a wolf, wearing the guise of a lamb.
134:
Hey, meanie! That's not very nice! 
Besides, you aren't the same person 
on the insi—
138:
Ah! You AREN'T the same on the inside. 
Are you a homunculus? No, that's not 
right. How does this work?
143:
Light is a great hero, but he was flung 
far from his home world. We travel 
now to find that world.
147:
You're quite the intriguing specimen 
yourself...
150:
Looking into other worlds, are you? 
Perfect. Then I shall join you on your 
quest.
161:
Hunh? Listen, I'm doing you a favor. 
Turn it down... and you might regret it.
164:
Oh, shoot. Then I meant to say, happy 
to have you on the team. Haha... ha...
168:
My name is Stella. This is Light and Alk. 
You are welcome to join us.
173:
See? That's more like it! I just know 
we're all going to be best friends 
forever!
